# AtomicU8 in std::sync::atomic - Rust

```
#[repr(C, align(1))]pub struct AtomicU8 { /* private fields */ }
```

Expand description

An integer type which can be safely shared between threads.

This type has the same size and bit validity as the underlying integer type, [`u8`](../../primitive.u8.html "primitive u8").

For more about the differences between atomic types and non-atomic types as well as information about the portability of this type, please see the [module-level documentation](index.html "mod std::sync::atomic").

**Note:** This type is only available on platforms that support atomic loads and stores of [`u8`](../../primitive.u8.html "primitive u8").

